pageContext.claim: “Every major Democrat running for President supports a massive government takeover of health care that would raid Medicare forced private doctors out of medicine and lead to the rationing of life saving treatments. And you know they're going to take away your private health care, your private insurance.”
pageContext.analysis: Some Democrats, especially in the House, have rallied around a proposal called "Medicare for all" championed by Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-Vt.). The plan would eliminate private plans and create national health insurance. But it's false to say a majority of Democratic candidates in 2018 supported this concept, especially in the Senate.
